ss or theft. However, even if I\u0026#39;m not actively using an old device and it\u0026#39;s just gathering dust, I still like to keep it registered on \u0026#34;Find My Device\u0026#34; for the reasons below.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"i-can-track-and-recover-my-devices\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e1 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            I Can Track and Recover My Devices\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne of the main reasons I never remove any of my old devices from \u0026#34;Find My Device\u0026#34; is for tracking and recovery purposes. Even if I\u0026#39;m not using some of these devices regularly, they still serve as backup options or are passed on to family members. As a result, my old devices sometimes end up in unexpected places—like a forgotten drawer at the office or left behind at a friend\u0026#39;s house.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eBeing able to \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/tag/how-to-trace-a-mobile-phone-location-with-google-latitude/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003elocate my devices remotely\u003c/a\u003e spares me the hassle of retracing my steps or guessing where they might be. It\u0026#39;s a bit of extra insurance that costs me nothing and has saved me more than once from permanently losing a device.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"i-can-remotely-lock-my-device-and-wipe-data\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e2 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            I Can Remotely Lock My Device and Wipe Data\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;Gorodenkoff\\/\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026#34;https:\\/\\/www.shutterstock.com\\/image-photo\\/home-office-man-using-desktop-computer-2193418169\\\u0026#34; rel=\\\u0026#34;noopener noreferrer\\\u0026#34; target=\\\u0026#34;_blank\\\u0026#34;\u0026gt;Shutterstock\u0026lt;\\/a\u0026gt;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"google and apple find my device logos with man checking website for lost phone\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/google-and-apple-find-my-device-logos-with-man-checking-website-for-lost-phone.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                        \u003cfigcaption\u003eGorodenkoff/\u003ca href=\"https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/home-office-man-using-desktop-computer-2193418169\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eShutterstock\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e In case one of my devices gets stolen or lost, having it registered with \u0026#34;Find My Device\u0026#34; allows me to remotely lock it down immediately. This feature helps me \u003ca href=\"http://www.makeuseof.com/how-remotely-disable-smartphone-android-iphone-samsung/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eprevent unauthorized access by setting a passcode or locking the screen\u003c/a\u003e, even if I no longer have the device physically. If I believe it\u0026#39;s lost and not stolen, I can also display a custom message on the screen with contact information for its return, all while keeping the rest of my data safe.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eIf things take a turn for the worse—like if I\u0026#39;m convinced the device is truly gone for good—I can take it a step further and erase all of the data remotely. This is a lifesaver, especially considering how much personal and sensitive information we store on our devices these days.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThis way, even if someone manages to access the device, they won\u0026#39;t have access to my photos, documents, or account logins. They won\u0026#39;t even be able to answer calls, read any notifications, or steal my identity in any way. That level of protection helps me sleep better at night.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"it-maintains-activation-lock-for-security\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e3 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            It Maintains Activation Lock for Security\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;DALL-E\\/MakeUseOf\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Different devices displaying an encryption lock display\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/how_does_encryption_work_is_encryption_actually_safe.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                        \u003cfigcaption\u003eDALL-E/MakeUseOf\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKeeping my old Apple devices in \u0026#34;Find My\u0026#34; also helps maintain iCloud\u0026#39;s Activation Lock, which is a crucial security feature. Likewise, removing my old Android phone or tablet from \u0026#34;Find My Device\u0026#34; by removing the Google account also disables FRP (Factory Reset Protection). For this reason, I find it \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/dont-remove-lost-iphone-from-icloud/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ebest not to remove the device from my account even if it\u0026#39;s lost\u003c/a\u003e and I\u0026#39;ve erased it remotely.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe security features I mentioned above stay active as long as the device remains linked to my account. As a result, even if someone gets hold of my device, they can\u0026#39;t simply wipe it and repurpose or resell it without entering my credentials.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"it-retains-access-to-imei-for-recovery\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e4 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            It Retains Access to IMEI for Recovery\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;Reezky Pradata\\/\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026#34;https:\\/\\/www.shutterstock.com\\/image-photo\\/detail-photo-imei-code-on-mobile-1667711677\\\u0026#34; rel=\\\u0026#34;noopener noreferrer nofollow\\\u0026#34; target=\\\u0026#34;_blank\\\u0026#34;\u0026gt;Shutterstock\u0026lt;\\/a\u0026gt;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1199\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"IMEI number on an Android phone\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/imei-number-on-an-android-phone.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                        \u003cfigcaption\u003eReezky Pradata/\u003ca href=\"https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/detail-photo-imei-code-on-mobile-1667711677\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eShutterstock\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/tag/phones-imei-makeuseof-explains/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eThe IMEI (International Mobile Equipment Identity) number\u003c/a\u003e is a unique identifier for every mobile device, and it can be incredibly useful in recovery situations. Keeping my old devices listed in the \u0026#34;Find My Devices\u0026#34; list gives me a central and easily accessible place to retrieve critical information like the IMEI.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eHaving the IMEI on hand is a huge advantage if my phone is ever lost. Reporting the IMEI to authorities or my mobile carrier can help blacklist the device, making it harder for anyone to use it on any network. Without \u0026#34;Find My Device,\u0026#34; I\u0026#39;d have to dig through old paperwork or linked devices to find this number—which isn\u0026#39;t always practical.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eKnowing I have a reliable method to locate and secure my devices gives me peace of mind, especially considering the sensitive information they often contain. Furthermore, there are no significant downsides to keeping them listed, which is why I firmly believe that keeping my old devices on \u0026#34;Find My Device\u0026#34; is a wise decision.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n        \n\n    \n\n        \n\n\n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
